<section xmlns="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/dc-library" xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" containing-doc="D.C. Code">
  <num>4-221.01</num>
  <heading>Severability.</heading>
  <text>Should a court of competent jurisdiction hold any provision of this chapter to be invalid, then the remaining provision of the chapter shall be considered to be severable and given full effect.</text>
  <annotations>
    <annotation doc="D.C. Law 4-101" type="History" path="§2201">Apr. 6, 1982, D.C. Law 4-101, § 2201, 29 DCR 1060</annotation>
